title: Beware of Banjo
description:
In 2008, I locked myself in A room with a banjo and this is what came out. This is NOT typical, out of tune, twangy banjo music. I would say this is relaxing, acoustic, instrumental music. I made this as a solo project while performing with The Doerfels, the band I started with four of my younger brothers and our only sister. 
Anyways, If you dare to listen, Beware of Banjo!
If you receive any value from this music, which I loved making, please let me know with any kind of value! ITM TYFYC KTLD,
Sir TJ The Wrathful

title: Good Morning
description:
Good Morning is an electronic instrumental record that awakens the senses with its vibrant and uplifting soundscapes. From the very first track, the listener is immersed in a world of pulsing rhythms, shimmering synths, and melodic hooks that capture the energy and optimism of a brand new day.
The record's sonic palette is diverse, drawing from a range of electronic sub-genres including ambient, house, techno, and trance. Each track is carefully crafted with meticulous attention to detail, resulting in a cohesive and seamless listening experience that takes the listener on a journey through a kaleidoscope of moods and emotions.

title: Home Sweet Home (The Dream of Love Survives but it Disappoints Constantly)
description: As you press play on "Home Sweet Home (The Dream of Love Survives but it Disappoints Constantly)," the opening notes of the electronic instrumental album send a shiver down your spine. The haunting melodies and dissonant harmonies seem to echo through the empty spaces of a world long forgotten, evoking images of a desolate landscape where hope and happiness are distant memories. The album's electronic instrumentation is both eerie and ethereal, capturing the shattered and broken nature of a dystopian world in a hauntingly beautiful way. The persistent dream of love that survives, but disappoints constantly, is a poignant reminder...

title: The Lightningrod Salesman - Hiddenkind
description:
Dive into this lush world of musical experimentation, where real instruments mix with electronic ones, where beauty and fear struggle for dominance, where nature and song breathe warm life into the cold climate of synthetic sounds.
The concept for this album starts with the idea of a tribe in the isolated jungle, hidden away from civilization, practicing the old, beautiful ways of survival.
From there it may take you many places.
Enjoy
